HEADWORD: Triduan
<hw>Trid"u*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>triduanus</ets>, fr. <ets>triduum</ets> space of three days;
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>dies</ets> day.]</ety> <def>Lasting three lays;
also, happening every third day.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Blount.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
